        "header": "3Motivation",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.08982/2603.08982v1/x2.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:Existing methods and top-ppselection fall short:dropping \"low-score\" blocksanderror-unaware block selectiondegrade the error-density trade-off. (a) Original attention map.\n(b) Permuted map after semantic-aware clustering.\n(c) Ignoring low-score blocks causes a large, sparse attention error.\n(d) Linear compensation with cluster means still yields high error due to naive top-ppselection.\n(e) Our method improves both error and density by routing based on the gap between full computation and compensation.",
                "position": 412
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "header": "4Methodology",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.08982/2603.08982v1/x3.png",
                "caption": "Figure 3:Overview ofSVG-EAR(a) The attention map after semantic-aware clustering.\n(b) Block error estimation. Using the cluster mean as a proxy for individual queries, the block error is computed via the sum of squared differences between exponentiated logits of individual keyskjk_{j}and the key meank¯\\bar{k}, then normalized by the block area to determine the error-to-size ratio.\n(c) Blocks with the highest error-to-size ratio are greedily selected for exact attention within the budget, while the rest are assigned to linear compensation.",
                "position": 475
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.08982/2603.08982v1/x4.png",
                "caption": "Figure 4:Visualization of attention maps from specific attention heads in Wan2.2 during text-to-video generation. (a) Original attention maps with sparse patterns, using heatmaps to represent attention weights. (b) Permuted attention maps. Following SVG2, we permute the attention maps such that attention begins to cluster into specific blocks. (c) Applying SVG2’s top-ppselection to these permuted attention maps, which ignores the sparse attention mechanisms of the remaining blocks. (d) Applying our Error-aware Routing and Mean Compensation mechanisms to the permuted attention maps, achieving higher attention map similarity.",
                "position": 667
            }
        ]
    },
